      "rationale": "Each of the three modeling teams performed an independent review of boundary conditions, material assignments, contact definitions, and loading protocols against the documented simulation plan. Cross-team comparison identified and resolved two minor discrepancies in contact stiffness settings prior to final runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model form",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Physics of large-deformation elasto-plastic contact captured; constitutive model validated against coupon-level data; geometric fidelity confirmed against CT measurements.",
      "rationale": "Elasto-plastic material model (bilinear isotropic hardening) calibrated against Ti-6Al-4V tensile coupon data. Contact between screw and UHMWPE block modeled with augmented Lagrangian formulation. Geometric dimensions verified against CMM measurements of production screws. Model form is appropriate for the compression-bending regime of interest."
