      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Test conditions span the range of COU loading scenarios; at minimum two distinct load levels or configurations tested.",
      "rationale": "Testing performed under a single ASTM F1717 standard configuration (10 mm offset, quasi-static compression-bending). Only one test condition evaluated, whereas the COU encompasses a range of surgical loading scenarios. Achieved level (2) is below required level (3); this is a known gap accepted by the assessment team given the standardized nature of F1717 and the conservative single-condition approach."
    },
