      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Quantitative comparison of all three QoIs (stiffness, yield force, force at 40 mm) against experimental data using pre-specified metrics; E/uval < 1.96 for all QoIs.",
      "rationale": "All three QoIs compared quantitatively against N=11 experimental measurements. Mean absolute percentage error: stiffness 4.7% (pooled), yield force 5.2%, force at 40 mm 6.8%. E/uval ratios: 1.41, 1.38, 1.52 — all below the 1.96 threshold. Comparison methodology pre-specified in the validation plan prior to test data unblinding."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Relevance of the quantities of interest",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 3,
      "achievedLevel": 3,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "QoIs directly linked to clinical failure modes; construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement are mechanically relevant to the COU.",
      "rationale": "Construct stiffness governs load sharing with the fusion mass. Yield force predicts onset of permanent deformation. Force at 40 mm displacement captures post-yield behavior relevant to fatigue and fracture risk. All three QoIs are directly mechanically relevant to the pedicle screw compression-bending COU and are standard ASTM F1717 outputs."
    },
